{"id":987,"date":"2023-05-18T21:39:21","date_gmt":"2023-05-18T19:39:21","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/securenest.org\/?post_type=glossary&#038;p=987"},"modified":"2023-05-20T21:31:41","modified_gmt":"2023-05-20T19:31:41","slug":"non-custodial-wallet","status":"publish","type":"glossary","link":"https:\/\/securenest.org\/glossary\/non-custodial-wallet","title":{"rendered":"Non-Custodial Wallet"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>A non-custodial wallet is a type of digital wallet that enables users to have full control over their private keys and cryptocurrencies. This means that users don&#8217;t need to rely on a centralized platform or third-party service provider to manage their funds. Non-custodial wallets are often considered to be more secure and private than custodial wallets, as users can store their private keys on their own device and access their funds at any time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, non-custodial wallets also require users to take on more responsibility for the security and management of their funds. Users need to ensure that they keep their private keys safe and secure, as any loss or theft of these keys can result in the permanent loss of their funds.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, non-custodial wallets may require users to have some technical knowledge and understanding of the underlying blockchain technology, which can be a challenge for beginners or non-technical users. Despite the risks and responsibilities that come with non-custodial wallets, many cryptocurrency users prefer them because they provide greater control, privacy, and autonomy over their funds.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Non-custodial wallets allow users to participate in the peer-to-peer economy without relying on intermediaries or exposing their data to potential threats. Moreover, non-custodial wallets are often open-source and community-driven, which fosters a spirit of decentralization and collaboration in the cryptocurrency ecosystem.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":0,"template":"","categories":[24],"tags":[],"letters":[39],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/securenest.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/glossary\/987"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/securenest.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/glossary"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/securenest.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/glossary"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/securenest.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=987"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/securenest.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=987"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/securenest.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=987"},{"taxonomy":"letters","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/securenest.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/letters?post=987"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}